Loan Ledger — JSON Schema (v1.0.0)

Strict • Deterministic • Audit‑Ready

`json
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://gitdigital-products.github.io/schemas/loan-ledger-entry.schema.json",
  "title": "Loan Ledger Entry",
  "description": "Schema for validating a single row of the Founder Working‑Capital Loan ledger.",
  "type": "object",

  "required": [
    "Date",
    "Type",
    "Amount",
    "Category",
    "Purpose/Notes",
    "Source of Funds",
    "Receipt/Evidence Link",
    "Running Balance",
    "Reviewer",
    "Attachments"
  ],

  "properties": {
    "Date": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$",
      "description": "ISO‑8601 date (YYYY‑MM‑DD)."
    },

    "Type": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": [
        "disbursement",
        "repayment",
        "forgiveness",
        "correction"
      ]
    },

    "Amount": {
      "type": "number",
      "exclusiveMinimum": 0,
      "description": "Positive decimal amount."
    },

    "Category": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Category must match allowed values for the given Type.",
      "enum": [
        "hardware",
        "software",
        "services",
        "operations",
        "infrastructure",
        "repayment",
        "forgiveness",
        "correction"
      ]
    },

    "Purpose/Notes": {
      "type": "string",
      "minLength": 5,
      "description": "Clear description of the transaction."
    },

    "Source of Funds": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": [
        "personal-card",
        "personal-bank",
        "company-bank",
        "N/A"
      ]
    },

    "Receipt/Evidence Link": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "URL or N/A.",
      "pattern": "^(https://|N/A)"
    },

    "Running Balance": {
      "type": "number",
      "description": "Updated principal balance after this entry."
    },

    "Reviewer": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Founder initials.",
      "pattern": "^[A-Z]{1,4}$"
    },

    "Attachments": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Optional comma‑separated URLs or GitHub references.",
      "nullable": true
    }
  },

  "additionalProperties": false
}
`

---

What this schema enforces
- Correct column names  
- Correct data types  
- Allowed enums for Type, Category, and Source  
- ISO date format  
- Positive decimal amounts  
- Valid URL or N/A for receipts  
- Reviewer initials format  
- No extra fields  

This schema does not enforce running‑balance math or cross‑row logic — that belongs in your validator — but it enforces everything a single row can validate in isolation.

